1. Update Ubuntu packages
sudo apt update
2. Install GCC (GNU C Compiler)
sudo apt install build-essential -y
This installs:


GCC compiler


G++ compiler


make tools


required libraries


3. Check compiler installation
gcc --version
You should see the GCC version displayed.

Program 1: Hello World
Create the file
nano hello.c
Paste this code
#include <stdio.h>int main() {    printf("Hello World\n");    return 0;}
Save and exit


Press CTRL + O → Enter


Press CTRL + X


Compile the program
gcc hello.c -o hello
Execute the program
./hello
Output:
Hello World

Program 2: Addition of Two Numbers
Create the file
nano add.c
Paste this code
#include <stdio.h>int main() {    int a, b, sum;    printf("Enter two numbers: ");    scanf("%d %d", &a, &b);    sum = a + b;    printf("Sum = %d\n", sum);    return 0;}
Save and exit


CTRL + O → Enter


CTRL + X


Compile
gcc add.c -o add
Run
./add
Example:
Enter two numbers: 10 20Sum = 30

